hu.elte.txtuml.api

Class Event

  • java.lang.Object
    • hu.elte.txtuml.api.Event
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    ModelElement
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    Signal

    public class Event
extends java.lang.Object
implements ModelElement
    Base class for events in the model.

    Represents: event

    Usage:

    As Event is just a base class for events, it is not used directly to define certain kinds of events.

    Java restrictions:

    • Instantiate: disallowed
    • Define subtype: disallowed, inherit from its predefined subclasses, like Signal

    Note: the only event type currently implemented in txtUML is a signal event, which is represented by referencing its signal directly.

    See the documentation of Model for an overview on modeling in txtUML.

    Author:
    Gabor Ferenc Kovacs
